# Caddy reverse proxy — terminates HTTPS in front of the Tax Agent container so
# the browser treats the site as a secure context (required for microphone /
# voice input, which browsers block over plain http://).
#
# Caddy auto-provisions and renews a Let's Encrypt certificate for the hostname.
# Requirements on the EC2 instance:
#   - security group inbound: 80 and 443 open (in addition to the app's 8080)
#   - the hostname below must resolve to this instance's public IP
#
# --- Option A: nip.io (zero signup — the hostname encodes the IP) -------------
# Access the app at:  https://54.144.100.99.nip.io
54.144.100.99.nip.io {
    encode gzip
    # flush_interval -1 keeps SSE chat tokens streaming (no buffering).
    reverse_proxy localhost:8080 {
        flush_interval -1
    }
}

# --- Option B: your own domain / DuckDNS (more reliable certs) ----------------
# Point e.g. tax-agent.duckdns.org at this instance's IP, then use:
#
# tax-agent.duckdns.org {
#     reverse_proxy localhost:8080 {
#         flush_interval -1
#     }
#     encode gzip
# }
